<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My First Webpage</title>
    
    <style>
        /* This applies to the whole page */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        /* This styles the main container box */
        .container {
            background-color: white;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto; /* Centers the box on the screen */
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0px 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        /* This styles the main heading */
        h1 {
            color: #2c3e50;
            text-align: center;
        }

        /* This styles the paragraph text */
        p {
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        /* This styles the interactive button */
        .my-button {
            display: block;
            width: 200px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: #3498db;
            color: white;
            text-align: center;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-weight: bold;
            transition: background 0.3s ease;
        }

        /* This changes the button color when you hover over it */
        .my-button:hover {
            background-color: #2980b9;
        }
    </style>
    </head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>Welcome to My Webpage!</h1>
        <hr>
        <p>This is a basic example showing how <strong>HTML</strong> and <strong>CSS</strong> work together. HTML handles the actual words and structure, while CSS makes it look beautiful with colors, spacing, and layouts.</p>
        
        <p>Here is a list of things you can do with CSS:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Change background and text colors.</li>
            <li>Adjust fonts and text sizes.</li>
            <li>Create spacing (padding and margins).</li>
            <li>Add shadows and rounded corners.</li>
        </ul>

        <a href="#" class="my-button">Click Me!</a>
    </div>
    </body>
</html>
